It was quite the fight to get cs_veristy compiled in hammer. Constant compile errors, one prop with a bad value crashing the damn map, issues with hostages not moving through doorways properly... After a while I couldn't get the damn .vmf to open in the SDK like it used to. Some update fucked it all up. Turns out the Hammer I needed hides in a \bin\ now. I gave up on this map quite a few times but finally the essentials are done. The outer city surrounding the map leaves much to be desired in the looks department but hopefully the layout is fine for big team fights. 

I couldn't figure out how to prevent the fireplace from projecting light onto the building across the street (seen in screenshot) and the snow seems unusually bright. It can be a problem if you're trying to see how much money you have.


Credit to aFreindlyCow who placed some props to the right of CT spawn's alleyway. Though I did everything else, he was going to help me finish the map further but got banned. Rest in peace my milky man.

The cs_varasto_bysleepy is a fast paced map, wich is very easy to learn. The CTs are attacking to a warehouse seized by the terrorists, the terrorists also have captured some of the warehouse workers.

This map is great for small battles due to it's small size. But it also is good for big battles. The rounds are usually very fast and full of action. CTs have to move from their spawn quickly or they will get pinned down by the terrorists.

There are 3 routes to the warehouse. First and Second are through the warehouse's loading platform. The third route is through a dark tunnel wich is a good way to sneak to the terrorist's back, but if you're spotted in the tunnel you will easily get killed because there is little cover in the tunnel.

PS. This is my first map to be uploaded so be gentle :D
Enjoy!

This was something I modeled back in June/July of 2008. It's an accurate recreation of the Walter Pyramid at CSULB when I used to go there. I used this map in one of my class projects and haven't modified it since. I did all of the mapping, texturing and the modeling for the various props (trashcans, friend's car, etc.) I planned to finish it then but never got around to.

The tubular railing were really difficult to create because of the odd angles they bent in and an editor like Hammer just made it even harder. I considered making them into props but there would have been way too many props to make. Despite the map being a huge open area, I managed to optimize it so that it would only render what is visible. The inside of the building is only rendered when the doors are open.

The inside of the pyramid is still incomplete because I don't have enough photo reference. The "green side" of the pyramid is also incomplete. There is a handicap access ramp that is supposed to be there. So far, only the doors on the "yellow side" open. I meant to have the hostages inside the building once it was completely modeled and you had to help bring them out so I'm not even sure how playable this map really is.

Anyhow, if you've never seen the building in person, here's your next best chance. :P

EDIT: Perhaps I should finish this map sometime because I had no idea that the floorplans to every single building on campus, including the pyramid, was publicly available on the uni's website... So many rooms...

This map has a relativly simple formula. Like most hostage rescue maps, the CTs have to assault the building from multiple points, grab the hosties and not die in the process. There are two ways to enter the building for the CTs, either through the front door or the side door/ladder. Both are very close to the terrorist spawn point, and a slow CT team will be cut off in no time. The counter-terrorists really have to work as a team here to win, since the map has so many narrow staircases and hallways with quick turns. This map isn't the best one around, but it is very popular, so I decided it would be best to review and add it here.

Terrorists have taken control of the mayors house in a sleepy little village in Tuscany, Italy.

Counter-Terrorist operatives have been deployed by the castle grounds ready to move in and escort the hostages to safety.



Terrorist Objectives:

Counter-Terrorist Objectives:

Ensure that the Terrorists are wiped our or rescue the hostages within the time limit given.

It's amazing how a map can evolve. 
This, for example, began as a coop project by myself and Urby under the working title "ss_pijamas." 
The "ss" stood for Silent Strike which was an experimental gamemode we discovered quite by chance in which players only have 15hp, and CTs are limited to silent weapons and are outnumbered by terrorists to a ratio of around 3:1. It proved to be exceptionally fun, but these sort of things tend to be a love or hate deal - so it was changed back to regular ol' CS. 

This map has been featured in several Scotch and Coffee videos, and contains the SnC offices. 

There are tens of easter eggs and secret areas, a proper radar with nav locations and more custom materials than you can shake a stick at. 

Enjoy. 


P.S. Urby's office was made by him. That is all. So much for "coop" the lazy bastard ;D
